    <h2>Company History</h2>
    <div class="history-statement">
        <ul class="history">
            <li>In July 2015, Nidhi Pai founded Accuracy Accounting in Atlanta, Georgia under the mission of creating an accounting firm that can offer unmatched efficiency, confidentiality, and adaptability. Our company started out relatively small with only a select team of talented CPAs, including Nidhi herself. </li>
            <li>
                In January 2016, our firm won the Atlanta business start up award for “Best Start Up Accounting Firm 2015” while also getting nominated for “Business with Best Service 2015”. To win an award like this after only five months since founding is an achievement that we wear with pride here at Accuracy Accounting. 
            </li>
            <li>
                Since our values lie in providing extraordinary service, we decided to give back to our community in the form of a partnership with Georgia Future Business Leaders of America (GA FBLA) in September 2016. We began to help fund the best and the brightest high school students in their business pursuits as a way to give back to our community. 
            </li>
            <li>
                As we continue to grow as a business, we also become increasingly interconnected with businesses in Atlanta. At the start of 2017, we were already helping a significant portion of businesses in our area with their accounting, and it has allowed us to place among the top ten Southeast accounting firms in July 2017.
            </li>
            <li>
                Our growth as a firm has prompted us to further our involvement in the community, as we would not be where we are without them. In November 2017, we decided to continue extending opportunities to high school students, and so we began to offer summer and winter internships.
            </li>
        </ul>
        
